genresAdvancedInfo.name: musica prehispanica
genresAdvancedInfo.description: This genre of music is a form of traditional music from the indigenous peoples of Mexico and Central America. It is characterized by the use of instruments such as flutes, drums, and rattles, and often includes vocal performances. The music is deeply rooted in the culture and history of the indigenous peoples and reflects their beliefs and traditions.
